This is an automation tool designed to fetch span loss from DWDM longhaul repeater nodes with Ribbon Communications as a vendor
It eliminates repetitive GUI clicks across multiple windows and provides a clean, reliable, and fast way to collect optical parameters from network devices.
The tool is built using expect for automated SSH interactions, making it suitable for large-scale NOC operations.

Features

SSH into multiple Ribbon Apollo RCPs simultaneously

Fetch optical parameters such as span loss from Add/Drop nodes

Supports models: Apollo 9608, 9624, 9603

Runs directly on EMS-STMS

Eliminates manual GUI navigation, improving efficiency and reducing errors

Timeout and error handling for unattended execution

Usage

Clone the repository:

git clone git@github.com:cheruiyot7693/noc-automation-scripts.git
cd noc-automation-scripts


Make the script executable:

chmod +x e3.sh


Run the script on EMS-STMS:

./e3.sh


The script will SSH into the configured RCP nodes and fetch optical parameters. Output is printed in a clean, easy-to-read format.

Configuration

Timeout: Set in the script using:

set timeout 20


Node List: Modify the script to include the RCP IPs or hostnames to target multiple Add/Drop nodes.
